Let $f(x)$ be a function representing the cumulative impact of a digital marketing manager's social initiatives, where $x$ represents time in months. Suppose that the function $f(x)$ is twice continuously differentiable and satisfies the following conditions: 
\begin{align*}
f(0) &= 0, \\
f'(0) &= 2, \\
f(\pi) &= 0, \\
f'(\pi) &= -2.
\end{align*}
Also suppose that the manager's social initiatives impact follows the harmonic motion which can be described by the equation
\begin{align*}
f''(x) + f(x) = 0.
\end{align*}
Find the function $f(x)$.
